design program personal statements events at stanford design program personal statements facebook twitter email print add to calendar personal statements is an event that celebrates the ingenuity and unique personalities of the second year design students in the form of a two week open ended project each student will use this forum to introduce themselves to the design community past projects have included swirling vortices of water with flaming jets erupting from the center and a life size replica of the wright brothers first airplane although the projects are different every year there will most definitely be demos and visually engaging displays please join us for stanford design program's biggest event of the year when friday december 9 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 3 hour s where design loft courtyard building 610 map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags other sponsor design group mechanical engineering contact mkosterich stanford edu or mzahedi stanford edu admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 299 29997 last modified november 22 2011
